    Onboarding API

    Onboarding API Specifications

    Version: 2016-08-18

    Security

    api_key

    (api key)

    Pass the Authorization header in your request as "Authorization: Token INSERT_KEY_HERE. Contact Bambora to get an API Key generated for you if you don't have one.

    Name In
    api_key header

    Operations

    Funds Transfer (SEPA-EUR)

    POST

    /v1/boarding/workflows/sepa-eur/applications
    Description

    Creates a new SEPA-EUR application. The state of the application will be returned in a successful request. The response will include an application id that should be used for all future requests to that application.

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/sepa-eur/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    Parameters

    No parameters

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/ach-usd/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    No parameters

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/eft-cad/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/psp-usd/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    Parameters

    No parameters

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/gw-cdn/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    Gateway application (GW-USA)

    POST

    /v1/boarding/workflows/gw-usa/applications
    Description

    GET

    /v1/boarding/workflows/gw-usa/applications
    Description

    Retrieves all applications referenced by the given criteria in the url. A search criteria can be a combination of the following:

    • state={state}
      • Accepted values are "in_progress", "in_review", "on_hold", "approved" and "rejected"
    • created_before={date}
    • created_after={date}
    • updated_before={date}
    • updated_after={date}

    Documents file data will be excluded to limit the amount of data on the wire.

    Parameters

    No parameters

    200 Application(s) retrieved Array of GwUsaApplicationResponse
